	<h3> Web Accessibility </h3>
	<hr class="color-tag">

	<p class="index-intro" style="padding-bottom:15px"> 
		This project is dedicated to <code>web accessibility</code>, and how to incorporate more accessibility features into web development. Well-done accessibility can be done by creating a balance between your project’s content and your user’s needs. I’ve included four web applications, showcasing ways to include these features into your own web applications. 
	</p>

	<h4> Google Speech and Twilio App </h4>
	<p style="padding-bottom:15px"> This application combines both Google Speech-to-Text and Twilio APIs. This application turns audio speech and sends it as a text message to a mobile phone. <span> Learn more about the Speech to Mobile Text </span>
		<%= link_to "Twilio Demo", capstone_twilio_path, {:class => "index-project-link reverse"} %>. <br>
	</p>

	<h4> Google Speech to Email App </h4>
	<p style="padding-bottom:15px"> This application combines the power of Google Speech-to-Text API with the functionality of email. Instead of typing your message, you can speak to your computer microphone with the body message. <span> Learn more about the</span>
		<%= link_to "Speech to Email Demo with Google API", capstone_email_path, {:class => "index-project-link reverse"} %>. <br>
	</p>

	<h4> Google Translate for Web Translation </h4>
	<p style="padding-bottom:15px"> This application shows the simplicity of adding a Google Translate plug-in to make websites multilingual friendly, and to intice non-English speakers. <span> Learn more about creating a </span>
		<%= link_to "Multilingual Site", capstone_translate_path, {:class => "index-project-link reverse"} %>. <br>
	</p>

  <h4> WIA-ARIA and CSS </h4>
	<p style="padding-bottom:15px"> This application shows some common WIA-ARIA and CSS Accessibility features you can add to your website. <span> Learn more about </span>
		<%= link_to "ARIA and CSS for Accessible Web Design", capstone_css_path, {:class => "index-project-link reverse"} %>.
	</p>

